<chapter condition="TITLE=System Features - Static Data;PERM=sy_data_access;ACCESS=SY_DATA"
         role="TOPIC">
  <title>Data Maintenance Module</title>

  <para>This module differs from the most of the modules described in this
  book, in that it is targeted to a slightly different type of bank
  administrator. It is not on the <xi:include href="../entities_en.xml"
  xpointer="ent_System_F" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"/> menu
  but the <xi:include href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_Middle_Office"
  xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"/> menu. It is made available to
  more users than are the modules that deal with jurisdiction and the
  maintenance of customers, banks and users.</para>

  <para role="TEXT">As an administrator at a bank, you use the
  <application>Data Maintenance</application> module to maintain various lists
  of data useful to your bank - details of counterparties, frequently used
  phrases, and so on.</para>

  <para role="TEXT">These are the lists that are invoked through popup windows
  in the transactional modules (see the <emphasis role="strong">User Manual -
  Bank</emphasis>), generally by clicking a magnifying glass icon. For
  example, in the <xi:include href="../entities_en.xml"
  xpointer="ent_Export_LC" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"/>
  module, the applicant is selected from such a list.</para>

  <section role="ITEM">
    <title>Functions</title>

    <para>The Data Maintenance functions are part of the <xi:include
    href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_Middle_Office"
    xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"/> menu. They are as
    follows:</para>

    <variablelist role="TEXT">
      <varlistentry>
        <term><guisubmenu>Counterparties</guisubmenu></term>

        <listitem>
          <para>Maintain the list of available customer counterparties, that
          is, companies that your bank can deal with. They can be
          beneficiaries of Letters of Credit, Banker's Guarantees and Fund
          Transfers, applicants of Export Letters of Credit (importers),
          transportation companies for Shipping Guarantees, or drawees for
          Export Documentary Collections.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term><guisubmenu>Banks</guisubmenu></term>

        <listitem>
          <para>Maintain the list of available bank counterparties, that is,
          banks that your bank can deal with. They can be, for example, the
          optional Advising Bank for a Letter of Credit, the Issuing Bank for
          an Export Letter of Credit notification, or the Presenting Bank for
          an Export Collection.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term><guisubmenu>Phrases</guisubmenu></term>

        <listitem>
          <para>Maintain the list of frequently used phrases. These are chunks
          of predefined texts that a user can include in the narrative fields
          that appear on many forms.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </section>

  <section>
    <title>Counterparties</title>

    <para>Maintain the list of available customer counterparties.</para>

    <para>When you select this option, you are presented with a list of all
    the existing customer counterparties. You can search the list by entering
    search criteria in the <guilabel moreinfo="none">Entity</guilabel> (if
    present), <guilabel moreinfo="none">Abbreviated Name</guilabel> and
    <guilabel moreinfo="none">Name</guilabel> fields at the top of the
    page.</para>

    <para>The list of existing customer counterparties has the following
    columns:</para>

